Rating: 3
I like this very much but found that I like it even more when I steep a few Saffron Threads in the Chicken stock,(homemade is a plus) add a minced clove of garlic about 30 seconds before the rice, and at the end add about a 1/2 cup of grated Parmesan and a teaspoon or so of butter along with the Basil and Pine-nuts. OK so it's a different recipe now. I also like to brown Chicken pieces or Pork Chops, put them aside, prepare the rice then nestle the meat in the rice before covering. When the rice is done remove the meat add the Basil, Cheese, Pine-nuts and Butter. let it sit for a couple minutes then serve on a platter with the meat arranged on top.

